# ── wheel build-time tool ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# `wheel` is a build dependency only (not at runtime). The privilege-
# escalation path requires a malicious .whl input, which we don't accept
# from untrusted sources at build time.
# Reviewed: 2026-05-21 — Louis
CVE-2026-24049

# ── mlflow CVEs requiring 3.x upgrade ─────────────────────────────────
# Our constraint is `mlflow>=2.22,<3`; all listed CVEs are fixed in 3.x
# (path traversal, SSRF, arbitrary file read, auth bypass).
# Compensating controls already in place:
#   - Server is bound to 127.0.0.1 only (phase 0.1)
#   - Basic auth required for all /api/* calls (phase 2.2)
#   - Server runs as non-root uid=10001 (phase 3.5)
#   - All capabilities dropped, no-new-privileges (phase 3.3)
# Tracked: migrate to MLflow 3.x as part of phase 6 (PostgreSQL backend +
# S3 artifact store) where the upgrade can be tested holistically.
# Reviewed: 2026-05-21 — Louis
CVE-2025-15031
CVE-2025-15036
CVE-2025-15379
CVE-2025-10279
CVE-2025-14279
CVE-2025-14287
CVE-2026-2033
CVE-2026-2393
CVE-2026-2614
CVE-2026-2635
CVE-2026-0596
CVE-2026-2652

# ── distroless base image (Debian 12 + CPython 3.11) ─────────────────
# These CVEs ship with the gcr.io/distroless/python3-debian12:nonroot
# digest we pin against. They are fixed upstream but the distroless
# build hasn't rebased yet. Compensating controls:
#   - Image runs as nonroot (uid 65532), read-only rootfs, all caps dropped
#   - The tarfile / email-header attack surface is unreachable from /predict
# Tracked: re-pin the distroless digest on every dependabot/PR review.
# Reviewed: 2026-05-21 — Louis
CVE-2026-0861
CVE-2025-13836
CVE-2025-8194
CVE-2026-1299

# ── Debian bookworm DSAs (May 2026) ──────────────────────────────────
# libgcrypt20 DoS via incorrect ECDH and krb5 remote DoS via NegoEx
# parsing. Both fixed in bookworm but distroless hasn't rebased yet.
# Same compensating controls as above: nonroot, read-only rootfs, caps dropped.
# Reviewed: 2026-05-26 — Louis
CVE-2026-41989
CVE-2026-40355

# ── gradio: optional academic dep only ────────────────────────────────
# `gradio` lives in the [academic] extra and is used solely by the legacy
# `app.py` notebook UI. It is NOT installed in the production runtime
# image (Dockerfile.api does not pull it). Fixes in gradio 6.x require
# a major bump which is unrelated to the production API.
# Reviewed: 2026-05-21 — Louis
CVE-2026-28414
